    "created_at": "2015-08-24T14:13:53Z",
    "updated_at": "2015-08-24T14:13:53Z",
    "body": "No, it is very easy to get your source code even when you packaged them in `asar` archive, the V8 JavaScript engine is never designed to hide source code. NW.js does succeed to hide one file of the source code completely, but with the price of significant performance downgrade.\n\nSo if you really to want to protect your source code, you have to write them in C++ and make a native Node module.\n"
  },
  {
    "url": "https://api.github.com/repos/electron/electron/issues/comments/134222313",
