    "created_at": "2016-07-27T08:43:11Z",
    "updated_at": "2016-07-27T08:43:11Z",
    "body": "@fritx, Node has a module called vm which can eval code. I guess you could find a way to call it or it's underlining C++ API from your addon and use that to load your code. \nKeep in mind that the user could still manage to open the developer tools and see the loaded script. Even if you manage to block that using a custom Electron build and the addon checking to see that your Electron build wasn't tampered with, the user could still see your code as a string in memory.\n"
  },
